    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that both points exist, but looking at it from a purely ethical standpoint, isn't one more \"correct\" in a modern context? like, most people agree that saving a life is a higher moral priority than enforcing a border law, right? so shouldn't the asylum side be viewed as the stronger moral position?",
