      "content": "but that feels like a false equivalence. one side is about following abstract laws and protecting borders, but the other is about actual human survival and preventing death. how can you equate a legal procedure with the lives of real people? isn't it actually a bit more \"valid\" to say that humanity should always come before bureaucracy?",
